        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertDateToStringDate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a date value into a string representation. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate logic that can be reused across queries. This function specifically focuses on transforming a date into a formatted string, which can be useful for display purposes or when interfacing with systems that require date values in a specific string format."
        }
