          "text": "Scalar functions can introduce performance overhead when used in large queries or applied to many rows, as they are executed row-by-row. However, for simple conversions like date formatting, the impact is generally minimal. It is important to ensure that the function is not used excessively in performance-critical queries, especially those involving large datasets. Using built-in SQL Server functions for formatting can help maintain efficiency."
